  "group": "CSS функции",
  "options": [
    {
      "text": "Запасной вариант для возможно неподдерживаемых единиц"
    },
    {
      "text": "Гарантировать, что единицы `vw` находятся в диапазоне от 20px до 50px"
    },
    {
      "text": "Линейная шкала от 200px до 500px"
    },
    {
      "text": "Логарифмическая шкала (основание 2) от 200px до 500px"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ошибка! Нет поддержки в IE 11"
    }
  ],
  "questionProse": [
    "Что делает функция `clamp()`?"
  ],
  "explanationProse": [
    "The `clamp()` function allows the width to scale based on `50vw`, but keeps it within a range of 200px to 500px.\n\n    This means the width will be 200px when 50vw would be less than 200px, 500px when 50vw would be greater than 500px, and linear between those limits.\n\n    It lets you be auto-magically responsive! The thing to know about `clamp` is it combines **fixed units** with **responsive or computed units.**\n\n    Normally you wouldn't want to use viewport units for font sizes, but with `clamp()` we can ensure the font size doesn't get too small or too large."
  ]
}
